    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="622"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d622">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 365.117/34.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Page</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 2, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>34. You telegram 30, September 21. Have repeatedly written, also made personal
                    visits, Foreign Office without reply or other result than promise to consider in
                    one case only. Am continuing efforts. Please instruct.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson Page</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
